               <head>Commentary on Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Taṣḥīḥ-i Mas̲navī by Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Kāẓim al-Ḥasanī al-Ḥusaynī al-Najafī "Fayz̤ān"</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1044B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7355">Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Kāẓim al-Ḥasanī al-Ḥusaynī al-Najafī "Fayz̤ān"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7355">محمّد هاشم ابن محمّد كاظم الحسنى الحسينى النّجفى فيضان </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22197">Taṣḥīḥ-i Mas̲navī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22197">تصحيح مثنوى</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Commentary on the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> of <persName key="person_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName> (d. 670/1271) by <persName key="person_f7355" role="aut">[Mīr Sayyid] Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Kāẓim al-Ḥasanī al-Ḥusaynī al-Najafī known as Fayz̤ān</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The title is a chronogram yielding the date 1122/1710-11. 
</p>
                        <p>This volume is defective, having lost a number of folios from the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 150v): completed by <persName key="person_f7144" role="scr">Ḥafīẓ Allāh al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, 18 Z̲ī [al-]Ḥijjah in RY 20 of <persName key="person_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName>, (1151)/29 March 1739. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking binding. 
</p>
                        <p>Loose folded paper wrapper (Acquittance Roll, Law Examination Committee, dated November [18]31; signed January 1833, Calcutta), watermarked; torn, stained, portions missing. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition very fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
